What you need to know:  It’s Nyahururu's Lucy Nduta, who braved stiff competition from Maurine Jepkoech from Elgeyo Marakwet in the last lap of two kilometres to win women’s Under-20 6km raceA fortnight after winning the national junior crown, Kibathi still had all the gas remaining in his cylinder to lead from gun-to-tape and emerge victorious in 24 minutes and 20 secondsNduta from Nyahururu clocked 21:13 to win the junior race, beating Jepkoech after a pulsating exchange of leads in the final phase of the race